          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            @fervour21- I think vision is an attribute which you can only refine not teach. It seems to be THE thing which separates the great from the very good and if it were teachable, I'm sure it would be the staple of big club academy instruction. I would guess it is the biggest cause of being released from a club as a child since it isn't teachable. Thiago could get stronger, because anybody can unless they are already at the ceiling for maximum possible human strength- Olympic weightlifters etc. I doubt he can improve his pace because his leg muscles seem to be slow-twitch-fibre dominant (as is evident by his stamina). Shooting is a technique which I believe you can improve almost infinitely but it requires willpower to do so and his game is primarily about creating not scoring so I just think he doesn't want to 'waste' time. In any case, his vision (which is not only passing but knowing where to be at a particular time, where players are without looking...) is in the top 1%.
